    thinking: "**Analyzing the Task\'s Requirements**\n\nI\'m starting by dissecting the user\'s request. I need to deliver a top-tier React portfolio website. Key inspiration lies in established designs, specifically those from Brittany Chiang, Sarah Dayan, and Bima Indra. The visual template provided in the image will be central to the project\'s aesthetics.\n\n\n**Exploring Available Skills**\n\nI\'m now focusing on available technical abilities. The aim is a fully interactive, dark/light mode site. I\'m prioritizing smooth scroll animations and CSS variable-based themes for consistent application. I\'ve noted the need for a PDF viewer modal for resume display, and I will be working on how to incorporate rendered visual content from the provided resume information. I am also planning consistent fonts and colors.\n\n\n**Evaluating Project Needs**\n\nI\'m now assessing the scope, which indicates a client-side React app is sufficient. No backend is needed, and I am avoiding `firebase-integration`, `focus-mode`, and a `gemini-api` backend, as these are unneeded for this project. Instead, I\'ll leverage local storage or client state for dark mode. I\'m checking the file structure, specifically `/metadata.json`, and will assess its contents soon.\n\n\n"
